"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1077154","Department for Transport","false","2019-02-28","<p>The Department is currently taking forward a number of road safety measures in accordance with its publicly stated road safety priorities, through the Road Safety Statement.</p><p> </p><p>In June last year, the Department issued a written statement to Parliament which included a progress report on the actions from that statement. Full details are available on the www.gov.uk website.</p><p>(<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/speeches/road-safety-recent-progress-and-future-work" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/speeches/road-safety-recent-progress-and-future-work</a>)</p><p> </p><p>The Department intends to publish a refreshed road safety statement and a two-year road safety action plan later this year.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1077154/answer",,,,,,"2019-02-28T15:55:57.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1077154/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1077154/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-02-25","Roads: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps is he taking to reduce the number of people killed and seriously injured on roads.","false","Biography information for Mr Tanmanjeet Singh Dhesi","Slough","Mr Tanmanjeet Singh Dhesi","225607"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1077155","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-02-28","<p>The information requested is not collected centrally.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1077155/answer",,,,,,"2019-02-28T17:18:29.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1077155/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1077155/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-02-25","Psychiatric Hospitals: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, on how many occasions were no mental health beds available for in-patient admissions in (a) Birmingham and (b) the West Midlands in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Liam Byrne","225416"
