"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1064924","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-03-04","<p>On 30 January, my Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care announced that the Pre-exposure Prophylaxis (PrEP) Impact trial would be expanded to 26,000 people. Work is underway with partners to take this forward. The PrEP Oversight Board has requested information on local capacity to make the additional places available and will review this shortly.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1064924/answer",,,,,,"2019-03-04T17:03:30.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1064924/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1064924/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-02-22","HIV Infection: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps he has taken to increase the number of places on the PrEP Impact Trial in (a) England and (b) Brentford and Isleworth constituency.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","224811"
